<Tool
  name="resume-resume"
  pip="pip install resume-resume"
  role="Agent Tool"
  repo="resume-resume"
  description="Post-crash Claude Code session recovery. Context survives the crash."
>
  <h2>What it does</h2>
  <p>Claude Code sessions crash. Context is lost. Work has to be re-explained. resume-resume captures session state so that when a session dies, the next one picks up where the last left off — with full context of what was being worked on, what was decided, and what's next.</p>

  <h2>Key features</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Session capture</strong> — records what was happening when the session ended</li>
    <li><strong>Context recovery</strong> — boot the next session with full prior context</li>
    <li><strong>Session search</strong> — find past sessions by topic, file, or date</li>
    <li><strong>Session analytics</strong> — timeline, insights, data science on your work patterns</li>
    <li><strong>MCP server</strong> — agents read and write session state through tool calls</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Install</h2>
  <pre><code>pip install resume-resume
claude mcp add resume-resume -- resume-resume-mcp</code></pre>

  <h2>Usage</h2>
  <pre><code># CLI — find recent sessions
resume-resume          # last 4 hours
cr 24                  # last 24 hours
cr --all               # everything

# MCP — from an agent
search_sessions  query: "eidos test where we beat claude"
merge_context    id: "session-123" mode: "hybrid"
session_timeline id: "session-456"</code></pre>

  <p>Full-text search across 5,000+ sessions in ~3 seconds using parallelized RRF. Summaries cached permanently after first generation. Follows continuation links across multi-session work.</p>
</Tool>
